{"rawJson":null,"m_plot":"As a kid, Charlie Banks (Jesse Eisenberg) both admired and feared the charismatic and violent local tough Mick Leary (Jason Ritter); in high school, Charlie witnesses Mick beat up two jocks at a party, leaving the two victims near dead. Despite Mick being the buddy of his best friend, Danny (Chris Marquette), Charlie reports Mick to the police. | Three years later, Charlie and Danny are college freshmen who are in for a surprise when Mick shows up for a visit. Though claiming to be visiting for the weekend, Mick moves into the two friends' dorm and begins borrowing their clothing, attending their classes, reading their books, and flirting with a woman (Eva Amurri) that Charlie has a crush on. Charlie begins to wonder if his friend has changed or if he is plotting a fiendish revenge against Charlie for turning him in to the police.","m_cast":"Jesse Eisenberg as Charlie Banks | Jason Ritter as Mick Leary | Eva Amurri as Mary | Gloria Votsis as Nia | Chris Marquette as Danny | Sebastian Stan as Leo | Dennis Boutsikaris as Mr. Banks | Charles Parnell as Assistant District Attorney Worsheck | Josh Richman as Professor Gersten | Steven Hinkle as Young Charlie Banks | Miles Chandler as Young Mick Leary | Cain Kerner as Young Danny | Sam Daly as Owen","m_reception":"The Education of Charlie Banks holds a 45% 'Rotten' rating on review aggregate website Rotten Tomatoes, with the consensus \"Unevenness and earnestness mire this otherwise sweet, surprising coming of age drama.\"[3]","m_production":null,"m_sequel":null,"m_based_on":null,"m_directed_by":"Fred Durst","m_produced_by":"Marisa Polvino Peter Elkoff","m_screenplay_by":null,"m_story_by":null,"m_starring":"Jesse Eisenberg","m_music_by":"John Swihart","m_cinematography":"Alex Nepomniaschy","m_edited_by":"Eric L. Beason","m_production_company":null,"m_distributed_by":"Anchor Bay Entertainment","m_release_dates":"April 27, 2007 (2007-04-27) (Tribeca Film Festival) | March 27, 2009 (2009-03-27) (Uni